According to the MongoCollection::group doc, there is a timeout setting for running group query (maxTimeMS). However in our case the execution always gets terminated with MongoCursorTimeoutException after just 0.5 sec irregardless of maxTimeMS setting.

{code}
	$_mongo_script_start = microtime(true);
	try {
		$res = $_mongo_conn->forum->stat->group(
			array('f' => true), // keys
			array('hits' => 0), // initial
			'function(doc, out) {if (doc.u != 1) out.hits+=doc.completed-doc.redir;}', // reduce
			array(
				'condition' => $condition,
				'maxTimeMS' => 20000,
				'socketTimeoutMS' => 20000
			)
		);
	}
	catch (MongoCursorTimeoutException $e)
	{
		$_mongo_conn_time = ceil((microtime(true) - $_mongo_script_start)*1000);

		echo "Mongodb group error getting views data after $_mongo_conn_time ms: " . $e->getMessage();
		exit;
	}
{code}

Script output:
Mongodb group error getting views data after 501 ms: 10.9.52.8:27017: Read timed out after reading 0 bytes, waited for 10.000000 seconds

10 seconds above is the socketTimeoutMS value in the connection options:

{code}
		$_mongo_conn = new MongoClient('mongodb://' . MONGO_HOST . '/?w=0',
			array(
				'connectTimeoutMS' => 100,
				'socketTimeoutMS' => 10000
			)
		);
{code}

But the script actually doesn't wait 10 seconds as evidenced by the microtime() timer. 

From the appropriate entry in the MongoDB server log it is clear the query usually runs for 1-2 seconds:
keyUpdates:0 numYields:58 locks(micros) r:2057614 reslen:37759 1120ms

If the query takes less than 500msec to complete, the error doesn't get thrown. So it appears there is a 500msec timeout constant hardcoded somewhere.

