With PHP-955, the native_long setting was turned on for 64-bit systems. Upgrading from 1.4.5 to a newer driver version, we discovered that ensureIndex() calls triggered by Doctrine no longer work:
{code} MongoResultException: localhost:27017: Index with name: testIndex already exists with different options{code}

This is the index as generated with native_long = 0 shown by getIndexes():
{code}{
    "v" : 1,
    "key" : {
        "a": 1,
        "b": -1
    },
    "name" : "testIndex",
    "ns" : "testdb.testcoll",
    "sparse" : false,
    "background" : true
}{code}

This is the index as created with native_long = 1:
{code}{
    "v" : 1,
    "key" : {
        "a" : NumberLong(1),
        "b" : NumberLong(-1)
    },
    "name" : "testIndex",
    "ns" : "testdb.testcoll",
    "sparse" : false,
    "background" : true
}{code}

Essentially, by having the native_long setting on, the index definitions are no longer compatible, which breaks index updates for us.
Disabling the setting is a workaround since that again breaks 64-bit support.

