updating MongoDB to version 3.0 results in an error if we want to fire a distinct command without any query parameter. Following code...

{code:php}
$db = \zMongo::getInstance()->selectDB('dbX');
$data = [];
$data['distinct'] = 'collectionX';
$data['key'] = 'keyX';
$data['query'] = [];

$res = $db->command($data);
var_dump($res, json_encode($data));
{code}

... produces following result:
{code:php}
array(3) {
  ["errmsg"]=>
  string(80) "exception: The query for the distinct command must be a document but was a Array"
  ["code"]=>
  int(18511)
  ["ok"]=>
  float(0)
}
string(55) "{"distinct":"collectionX","key":"keyX","query":[]}"
{code}

